# Test standards (studio)

- Prefer names like `test_[system]_[scenario]_[expectedResult]` (adapt to project test runner conventions).
- Arrange / act / assert structure; one logical assertion focus per test when practical.
- Unit tests avoid real filesystem/network unless explicitly integration tests.
- Integration tests clean up listeners, timers, and temp state.
- Performance tests record thresholds; fail when regressing beyond documented bounds.
- Regression test required for fixed production bugs when testable without heroic setup.
- Mock external I/O for fast deterministic runs.
